            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This is the logic also read the comments over there...\n```lua \nvim.cmd([[\n  command! Restart lua SaveAndRestart()\n]])\n-- Function to save session and restart\nfunction SaveAndRestart()\n\n-- Close NvimTree before saving session\n    local ok, _ = pcall(vim.cmd, \"NvimTreeClose\")\n    if not ok then\n        print(\"NvimTree is not loaded, skipping close.\")\nend\n\n    //Add on feature for saving sessions\n    -- Save the session to a specific location\n    local session_file = vim.fn.expand('~/.local/share/nvim/session.vim') -- You can change the path here\n-- Save session (force overwrite)\n    vim.cmd('mksession! ' .. session_file)                              -- Save session\n// Main code responsible for restart\n    **-- Call the restart shell script and exit Neovim\n    os.execute(\"~/.config/nvim/restart_nvim.sh\") -- Executes the shell script\n\n    -- Exit Neovim\n    vim.cmd('qa') -- Quit all windows and exit Neovim**\nend\n\n--this is the lua config in init.lua\n--what i did is:\n --on :Restart, SaveAndRestart get called and this function will open an isolated bash script which run even after the nvim editor get close  \n```\n```shell \n./restart_nvim.sh:\n#!/bin/bash\nSESSION_PATH=\"$HOME/.local/share/nvim/session.vim\"\n\n# Ensure directory exists\nmkdir -p \"$(dirname \"$SESSION_PATH\")\"\n\n\n# Load session only if it exists\nif [ -f \"$SESSION_PATH\" ]; then\n    nvim -S \"$SESSION_PATH\"\nelse\n    echo \"Session file not found!\"\n    nvim\nfi\n```\nThe issue was that trying to restart Neovim directly from the script failed because once Neovim exits, it cannot execute further commands. To solve this, a separate shell script was used:\n\nos.execute(\"~/.config/nvim/restart_nvim.sh\") runs the shell script, ensuring the restart process continues independently after Neovim exits.\nvim.cmd('qa') completely closes Neovim.\nThe shell script runs in the background and reopens Neovim in the current directory, restoring the session if available..\n**I hope this make sense.**",
